'''Beaver Creek Falls''', is a small [[waterfall]] located at the confluence of Beaver and Sweet Creeks in [[Lane County, Oregon|Lane County]], in the [[U.S. state]] of [[Oregon]]. The waterfall is known for joining of the two creeks becoming one intertwined waterfall.<ref>{{cite web|title=Beaver Creek Falls - Clatsop County, Oregon|url=https://www.waterfallsnorthwest.com/waterfall/Beaver-Creek-Falls-4703|website=Northwest Waterfall Survey|accessdate=5 June 2017}}</ref>

== Location ==
Beaver Creek Falls is located approximately 12 miles off of Highway 126, south of [[Mapleton, Oregon|Mapleton]]. It totals 20 feet fall in a wide cascade and is the centerpiece attraction of the Beaver Creek Falls Trail [[trailhead]] and Recreation Site.<ref name=alltrails>{{cite web|title=Beaver Creek Falls Trail|url=https://www.alltrails.com/trail/us/oregon/beaver-creek-falls-trail|website=AllTrails.com|accessdate=7 June 2017}}</ref>

