The '''geology of [[Republic of Artsakh|Artsakh]]''' is primarily part of the Kussary-Divichi Foredeep—the northern foredeep of the Greater Caucasus. The trough is filled with [[Oligocene]] to [[Quaternary]] age deepwater, [[molasse]] and marine sedimentary rocks. <ref>{{cite book |author=Moores, E.M.; Fairbridge, Rhodes W.|year=1997|title=Encyclopedia of European & Asian Regional Geology|publisher=Springer|p=61}}</ref>

