[[Category:Satellite meteorology and remote sensing]] [[Category:Remote sensing]]

'''Mt. Sisa''' is a heavily eroded [[pleistocene]] [[stratovolcano]] in [[Hela Province|Hela]], [[Papua New Guinea]]. The taller of the mountain's two main peaks is estimated to be {{convert|2650|m|ft|-1}} high.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://volcano.si.edu/volcano.cfm?vn=253801|title=Global Volcanism Program {{!}} Sisa|website=volcano.si.edu|language=en|access-date=2018-02-28}}</ref> The northern peak has a communications mast. The epicentre of the [[2018 Papua New Guinea earthquake]] was on the mountain's northern foothills.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://earthquake.usgs.gov/earthquakes/eventpage/us2000d7q6#executive|title=M 7.5 - 89km SSW of Porgera, Papua New Guinea|website=earthquake.usgs.gov|access-date=2018-02-28}}</ref>
